# T3 Stack Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- Full-stack TypeScript: Next.js (frontend) + tRPC (API) + Prisma (DB) + Tailwind (styling)
- Use `create-t3-app` for project initialization
- Type safety end-to-end: from database schema to UI components
- Auth: NextAuth.js with session-based or JWT strategy

## tRPC Integration
- Define routers in `src/server/api/routers/`
- Merge all routers in `src/server/api/root.ts`
- Use `protectedProcedure` for authenticated endpoints
- Use React Query integration: `api.router.procedure.useQuery()`

## Prisma
- Schema in `prisma/schema.prisma`
- Use `prisma.$transaction()` for atomic operations
- Seed data in `prisma/seed.ts`
- Run `npx prisma db push` for prototyping, `migrate` for production

## Best Practices
- Use Server Components for data fetching, Client Components for interactivity
- Validate inputs with Zod schemas shared between client and server
- Use environment validation with `@t3-oss/env-nextjs`
- Keep API procedures thin — delegate to service layer for complex logic
